I remember going on a naggy raid trying to land Ice comets on Fire Giants at 49. Couldnt land one the whole raid an naggy should be a raid for 50th lvs. Went back when I got Ice Lure, totalled 600-700dmg the whole raid with Ice Lures alone on Fire Giants. Severly piss poor when all your doing as a wiz is trying to dmg with spells. Needless to say experiences like that made me quit, cause you are totally worthless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uenoah35.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/02 1:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Resists</span><hr size=1> Since the new Resist system went live, there were some cases where I was resisted constantly from a light blue mob. This was a WL frost giant sentinel, was too busy fighting him so thought I just root and be on my way. The bastard resisted 10 roots! Soooo time to show who I was to him ( meet sunstrike ).<br>
<br>
Ice giants are resistant sometimes. I always rooted him before snaring him just incase. Never kite, nor quadded wyverns so I can't give any info on him (<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uteamnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teamnoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/5/02 1:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resists</span><hr size=1> I've been kiting since 28, reliably, and quadding since about 36 or so.  I find that the first level or two of a new camp shows me occasional resists, (about 1 in 8, or none for a couple quads, then 3 resists in a quad).<br>
<br>
After that I get about 1 resist per day, (100-150 pulls).  Bof only wears off prematurely for me if someone snares or darks the same mob.<br>
<br>
Mob choice is hugely important, though.  With jboots, I can't outrun frost giants in gd far enough to bof them.  so it's either bof on pull or I'm in trouble.  Oh, and I'm only targetting blue, generally lower blues.<br>
<br>
Awlin, 51. - born to solo <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=765.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=765.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=765.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=765.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=765.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=765.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General EQ Discussion<option value="graff